.SH NAME
_base_get_buffer_bar0 \- Calculates and Returns BAR0 mapped Host buffer address for the provided smid. (Each smid can have 64K starts from 17024)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __iomem *" _base_get_buffer_bar0
.BI "(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc "  ","
.BI "u16 smid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioc" 12
per adapter object
.IP "smid" 12
system request message index
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to buffer location in BAR0.
